:INFO
Community Clothing Swap
A clothing swap lets neighbors trade gently used clothing instead of discarding it. Events can be casual drop-in sessions or structured swaps with ticketed entry. Leftover items go to a local donation partner.

:COUNTER.half
3 Hours
Typical event duration
|
:COUNTER.half
50 Items
Minimum donation per participant for a fair swap

:PATH
Book the Venue
Description: Choose a community hall, library meeting room, or large backyard. Ensure good lighting, table space for sorting, and a fitting area with privacy.

:PATH
Sort and Display Clothing
Description: Organize items by type and size before doors open. Use racks, tables, and bins. Label sections clearly so guests can browse efficiently.

:PATH
Run the Event Day
Description: Welcome guests, explain swap rules, manage entry flow, and keep the space tidy. Assign volunteers to each section throughout the event.

:CHECKLIST
Event Prep Checklist
[ ] Confirm venue booking and access time
[ ] Recruit four to six volunteers
[ ] Collect clothing donations at least one week ahead
[ ] Set up racks, tables, and signage the morning of
[ ] Arrange a donation pickup for remaining items
[ ] Share event recap and photos to build momentum for the next one

:NOTE
A one item in, one item out rule keeps the swap fair and prevents hoarding. Offer a small raffle or community raffle for volunteers to boost participation.
